<TITLE> 3 killed in bus-truck crash at Bijoy Sarani </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 1 (bdnews24.com)Three bus passengers were killed and 15 people injured in a bus-truck collision in the capital early Sunday, said police. "As a Farmgate-bound passenger bus coming from Mirpur was negotiating Bijoy Sarani intersection at around 3am Sunday, a lorry laden with stone chips coming from Crescent Road direction hit it," Tejgaon police chief Lutfar Rahman told bdnews24.com. "Three bus passengers were killed on the spot." Md Choyon, 26, was the only one of the deceased to be identified immediately after the accident. The injured were admitted to different local hospitals for treatment. The truck driver fled the scene. Police seized both vehicles involved in the collision. bdnews
